[SPEAKER_13]: Are you guys doing, in Medford, regular meetings?

180
00:17:13,821 --> 00:17:15,623
[SPEAKER_13]: And do you have an email list?

181
00:17:15,703 --> 00:17:18,345
[SPEAKER_13]: And do you want people to be signing up to joining?

182
00:17:18,385 --> 00:17:25,429
[SPEAKER_13]: Like, how are you, like, are you like, oh, we want people to commit, or we just, we're creating a list and just getting as many people on it?

183
00:17:25,489 --> 00:17:28,331
[SPEAKER_13]: Like, what's, different groups do this different ways.

184
00:17:29,172 --> 00:17:33,215
[SPEAKER_13]: I was curious how you guys are, what's your approach and your approach here in Medford?

185
00:17:34,015 --> 00:17:35,076
[SPEAKER_05]: That's a great question.

186
00:17:35,096 --> 00:17:45,627
[SPEAKER_05]: I would say that our status is we're newly forming, and we recently, so to answer your question directly, we don't yet have an email list.

187
00:17:46,007 --> 00:17:55,657
[SPEAKER_05]: Mothers Out Front does have a general email list, and I believe that there are many members of Medford who are already connected, perhaps at the state level, to Mothers Out Front because

188
00:17:56,796 --> 00:18:00,237
[SPEAKER_05]: That's certainly a way in and there's a lot to become involved in.

189
00:18:01,378 --> 00:18:07,240
[SPEAKER_05]: There is a database that exists, some of which constitutes Medford residents.

190
00:18:07,580 --> 00:18:08,801
[SPEAKER_05]: We would like to add to that.

191
00:18:09,221 --> 00:18:18,405
[SPEAKER_05]: However, because we're so newly formed, barely formed in some ways, we haven't started to make a big recruiting push.

192
00:18:19,386 --> 00:18:25,291
[SPEAKER_05]: We're at the stage, I would say, just in my view of, you know, defining what we want to do.

193
00:18:25,571 --> 00:18:38,642
[SPEAKER_05]: And one of our next steps is going to be reconnecting with West Medford Community Center and kind of fleshing that out a little bit further for the year, which I think will then make more of a, I'm not even sure if recruiting is the right word, but

194
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:46,423
[SPEAKER_05]: an opportunity to try to engage people with some activities that might be laid out where we can kind of work together on those.

195
00:18:47,123 --> 00:18:56,107
[SPEAKER_05]: So I think we're a little bit early from the kind of trying to attract more people stage, but that is something that we probably will be planning to do.

196
00:18:56,447 --> 00:19:00,949
[SPEAKER_05]: And certainly that would be the long-term plan would be to engage as many people as we can who

197
00:19:02,694 --> 00:19:06,437
[SPEAKER_05]: who would like to work together in an inclusive way on some of these topics.

198
00:19:07,538 --> 00:19:16,565
[SPEAKER_05]: But we haven't started doing that kind of fully in earnest yet here in Medford because we've been still formulating our plans, if you will.

199
00:19:16,625 --> 00:19:27,934
[SPEAKER_05]: And, you know, I understand perhaps that, you know, some people may prefer to do actions as opposed to come to meetings and kind of talk about like what the plans could be.

200
00:19:29,331 --> 00:19:31,372
[SPEAKER_05]: So, but we do hope to be getting to that stage.

201
00:19:31,793 --> 00:19:48,141
[SPEAKER_05]: I think, you know, if within this year, even in the next, you know, few months with some plans, certainly that would involve, you know, planning a bigger and better pumpkin smash and maybe some related activities to really kind of further, you know, raise awareness about composting, et cetera.

202
00:19:48,221 --> 00:19:53,463
[SPEAKER_05]: So hopefully that will get started soon, but we're just at an early phase, if that makes sense.

203
00:19:54,263 --> 00:19:55,024
[SPEAKER_13]: It does, it does.

204
00:19:56,926 --> 00:20:00,708
[SPEAKER_13]: through my life been involved in the starting up of different organizations.

205
00:20:01,748 --> 00:20:02,288
[SPEAKER_13]: So I get it.

206
00:20:03,189 --> 00:20:04,970
[SPEAKER_13]: I will offer and share.

207
00:20:05,170 --> 00:20:19,836
[SPEAKER_13]: So this group can be utilized as a recruiting tool too to get the word out because this is a public group body and its meetings, I will remind everybody, are on TV, usually live.

208
00:20:20,056 --> 00:20:23,538
[SPEAKER_13]: Sometimes they get replayed if they're recorded for some reason.

209
00:20:25,899 --> 00:20:34,284
[SPEAKER_13]: Also, Lois and I have been managing for many years an email list called Go Green Medford, and it's got about 110 people on it.

210
00:20:35,325 --> 00:20:46,092
[SPEAKER_13]: The idea is we just push out green things of interest to the community, and another resident, Ken Kraus, will often just send things of interest there.

211
00:20:46,172 --> 00:20:52,196
